data.title: Maria Clementina of Austria (1798
data.meta_description: Archduchess Maria Clementina Franziska Josepha of Austria was the third surviving daughter of Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor, later Francis I of Austria after the dissolution of the Holy Roman Empire, and his wife Maria Theresa of Naples and Sicily, the eldest daughter of Ferdinand I, King of the Two Sicilies, and...
